uk.ac.brighton.uni.ab607.mmorpg.test.asn1

Class External

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.brighton.uni.ab607.mmorpg.test.asn1.External

  • public class External
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents external type, should be extended to allow getting real type of data, once External ends decoding. Decoding should be done as follows in subclass:
     <b>decode(){
   super.decode();
   if(super.getType == requiredType)
       this.decode();
   }else
   {
        //indicate error
   }
   </b>
    . Also encode/decode methods should be extended
    Author:
    baranowb, amit bhayani, sergey vetyutnev
